content.description: Stand/squat start laying back the right leaning arete, first move crux getting away from the rock to your left, then surf up the arete a few moves before you can pull an easy rockover mantle to end the climb.
content.location: Left side of the supercrack 2 boulder, starting at the lefmost end of the small corridor (if facing the wall).

content.description: Start standing in middle of Tall face. Make reachy moves between thin holds to reach big jug and crack above. Mantel to finish.
content.protection: Pads, hero spotters to avoid the death flake.
content.location: Middle of face in the corridor.

content.description: Start standing on left side of tall vertical face. Climb good holds to top.
content.protection: Pad, probably need good spot to avoid the death flake landing
content.location: Left side of wall in the corridor.

content.description: Obvious arching finger crack up the left face of the huge slab. Perhaps one of the only true highballs at Lincoln Woods. Back breaker rock blade below the crux topout.
content.location: Slab right of Bowling Pin boulder.  #1 on the beta photo.

content.description: Climb the left side of the slab staying right of Super Crack 2.
content.location: Left side of big slab, #2 on the beta photo.

content.description: From a sit start, climb up through scoop then bulge features on right side of tall face. Mantel and climb slab to top, or finish as for Super Crack II.
content.protection: Pad, hero spotters if finishing left over the death flake.
content.location: Right side of face in corridor.

content.description: Climb the obvious crack and flakes on the right side of the slab.  Rated 5.5 on the YDS.
content.protection: Pad, could be toproped but kind of short.
content.location: Right side of slab, #3 on the beta photo.

content.description: Seldom visited outcrops in the back of the park. Multi tiered rock with some highballs.
